<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="5" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="3.[788,1375,281,698]" lastBlockId="3.[167,1377,709,1368]" pageId="3" pageNumber="5">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[790,1053,281,306]" pageId="3" pageNumber="5">Descriptive notes.</emphasis>
Head-body 26 cm, tail 30 cm; weight 964 g. A medium-sized species with short, smooth fur, generally brown above and a lighter grayish-brown on the belly and ventral surface of the extremities. The face is demarcated into a mask, with whitish-gray markings along the jaw and throat from the chin to the ears. The dorsum of the head is brown with a black midline that is continuous for almost the entire length of the body. The ears are large and cup-shaped, being gray dorsally with black borders and (usually) a small cream-colored patch on the region beneath. The tail is brown proximally, gradually becoming a darker brown to black distally.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[173,723,827,856]" pageId="3" pageNumber="5" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph blockId="3.[167,1377,709,1368]" box="[173,723,827,856]" pageId="3" pageNumber="5">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[173,283,827,856]" pageId="3" pageNumber="5">Habitat.</emphasis>
Low-altitude coastal rainforest.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="5" type="food_feeding">
<paragraph blockId="3.[167,1377,709,1368]" pageId="3" pageNumber="5">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[173,435,862,895]" pageId="3" pageNumber="5">Food and Feeding.</emphasis>
There is no specific information available for this species, but it is presumably largely folivorous.
